description: It’s an action-packed issue of Batman Superman! In Batman Superman itself, the Man of Steel and Dark Knight try to help their equivalents on Earth 2! Injustice: Gods Among Us sees more betrayals between the heroes, while in Superman Wonder Woman, the couple must face the mystical Circe! And finally, we bring you the epic finale to the Ulysses storyline in Superman!

It’s an action-packed issue of Batman Superman! In Batman Superman itself, the Man of Steel and Dark Knight lose their memories, Injustice: Gods Among Us Batman steps up his campaign against his former friend!, while in Superman Wonder Woman, the power couple fight each other! In Superman the Man of Steel experiences life as a regular human! !

Following his popular appearances in the pages of DC Universe Presents: Justice League Trinity and his one-shot special earlier this year, The Flash is set to feature in his own ongoing series with DC Super Heroes: The Flash #1. Plus, every 76 page issue ofDC Superheroes: The Flash will feature Harley Quinn! Harley’s in for a big change as she starts a new life as a hero in her own unique way, in her very own solo story in each issue!

name: No. 28, 1987

description: So far, the Crime Syndicate have faced little resistance to their takeover of Earth and the resulting reign of terror. The tide is starting to turn in this issue of Justice League Trinity, however, as Batman and Lex Luthor’s resistance steps up a gear! Elsewhere, Stargirl and Martian Manhunter fight back against the Secret Society of Super Villains, and Cyborg goes through a serious upgrade! Plus, we find out the seriously dark origins of four of the Crime Syndicate’s members!

Forever Evil hots up this issue, as Batman, Lex Luthor and their Injustice League set their sights on the Crime Syndicate and prepare to storm the Watchtower! Meanwhile, Stargirl and a weakened Martian Manhunter tangle with the slippery Clayface and wrestle with their own nightmares! Cyborg has been rebuilt better than ever, but still needs help to beat Grid – could the mysterious Metal Men be the answer…?

It’s here! The final barnstorming part of ‘Forever Evil’! Batman, Lex Luthor and their Injustice League have come up against the Crime Syndicate, but with their mysterious prisoner Mazahs released, do they even stand a chance? Meanwhile, the new-look Cyborg and the Metal Men face the Syndicate’s Grid, and Stargirl must battle the manipulative Despero!

It's the start of an exciting new era for the Justice League! ‘Forever Evil’ is over, some members have left, and some very surprising members are joining up! Meanwhile, the members of the former Justice League of America pick up the pieces after their ordeal. What’s next could lie across the border in Canada! This issue also sees the return of the Justice League Dark, and true to form, they’re soon in big trouble. Plus, we also see the debut of the Flash in Justice League Trinity! You won’t want to miss a bit of it!
